      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WESTERN'S NASIAH (5) produced a modest effort most recently when eighth at Ballarat over 390m behind Come And See (22.70) in a Mix 3/4. Has ability and looks hard to stop. BELFAST SPOT (1) settled back off the inside but went through his gears strongly to find the frame with a 3 length third (28.65) at Bendigo in Grade 5. Hard to beat again. VIKING RULER (2) turned in a plain run last time when fifth at Sandown over 595m behind Crackerjack Gaz (35.15) in a R/A FIN. Placed at his previous run. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Must be included in calculations. URANA TAURUS (8) was in the money last start here at this trip - likely to feature again.",
